BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Vale Ferreira Speaks on Analyst Conference Call

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-27T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/brazil-daybook-vale-ferreira-speaks-on-analyst-conference-call.html
Vale SA’s new Chief Executive Officer
Murilo Ferreira speaks to investors and analysts on a conference
call at 8 a.m. Brazil time. Ferreira, who became CEO of the
world’s largest iron-ore producer on May 22, said last week the
company will maintain its $24 billion spending plan for the
year.  GOVERNMENT:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  meets with Health Minister Alexandre
Padilha at 10 a.m.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega attends a talk at the French --
Brazilian Chamber of Commerce at the Hotel Unique in Sao Paulo
at 11:30 a.m.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has meetings with
economists.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Second day of the Managing Capital Flows in Emerging Markets
conference in  Rio de Janeiro . Speakers also include
representatives of the  International Monetary Fund , local and
international banks.
*Latin Upstream conference in Rio de Janeiro, with Pemex
exploration director Carlos Morales and Colombian’s oil
association director Armando Zamora.  EQUITIES:
*Renova (RNEW11 BZ) approved 150 million-real loan from
Santander
*OGX (OGXP3 BZ) sold $2.56 billion of 7-Year bonds
*Banco Santander (SANB3 BZ) sold $200 million of additional 4.25
percent dollar-denominated notes due 2016, according to a person
familiar with the transaction.
*Cremer (CREM3 BZ) plans to sell 200 million reais in local
bonds, according to a regulatory filing.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 1.1 percent to 64,098.57.
*The real rose 0.9 percent to 1.6151 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
